cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with modeling and analyzing parallel systems, which can be considered as a type of control system. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The max-plus approach used in the paper is related to information theory and has been applied in various information processing problems. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper focuses on parallel systems and multi-stage fork-join networks, which are typical topics in distributed and parallel computing. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The end-to-end delay bounds derived in the paper are relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper provides statistical bounds of waiting and sojourn times, which are important performance metrics for parallel systems.
